  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihood Recovery Assistance to Conflict and Flood Affected Families of Shangla</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conflict and Flood Affected Families of Shangla</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of agriculture inputs (seeds and fertilizers) to the target farmers. Provision of fruit plants for horticulture promotion. Provision of vegetable seeds for kitchen gardening. Training of target farmers on integrated crop management. Provision of poultry inputs augmented with training on poultry management to the target beneficiaries. Provision of livestock breed improvement support. Provision of cash for work opportunities and cash grants to the target farmers and training of community organizations on Community Based Disaster Risk Management.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project has been planned to provide livelihood recovery support to the conflict and flood affected families of District Shangla through agriculture and livestock based interventions. Cash for work and cash grants have also been planned to support the marginalized/affected families.</narrative>
  </description>
